---
const features = [
  {
    title: 'Multi-layer playback',
    body:
      'Composite many video and image layers in real time with GPU blend modes, transparency, and frame-accurate scrub. Decode pipeline is per-clip and lock-free.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Professional codecs',
    body:
      'ProRes 4444 (with alpha), HAP, PNG sequences. Mixed frame rates handled natively — drop a 24fps clip on a 60fps timeline and it plays at its own rate.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Projection mapping',
    body:
      'Anchor-point calibration with a lens model. Soft-edge blending across multi-projector arrays. Persistent display identification by EDID.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Show-grade timing',
    body:
      'A dedicated show thread owns GPU compositing and output present. Editor modals, file dialogs, and resize loops never freeze the projectors.',
  },
  {
    title: 'OSC control',
    body:
      'Inbound OSC over UDP. Play, pause, seek, fire sections, jump to cues. Pairs natively with Bitfocus Companion for the rest of show control.',
  },
  {
    title: 'Projects travel',
    body:
      'A project is a folder. Copy it to a USB stick, sync to another machine, hand it to a collaborator — media, timeline, calibration, and settings move together as one tree.',
  },
];
---

<section class="features">
  <div class="features__inner">
    <p class="eyebrow">What it does</p>
    <h2>Designed around the live-show contract</h2>
    <p class="features__lede">
      Most media servers were built to make pretty things in software. entity
      was built around one rule: when the curtain goes up, the projectors must
      keep playing — even when the operator hits an OS dialog, plugs in a
      display, or scrubs the timeline mid-cue.
    </p>

    <div class="features__grid">
      {
        features.map((f) => (
          <article class="feature">
            <h3>{f.title}</h3>
            <p>{f.body}</p>
          </article>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .features {
    padding: 96px 32px 64px;
  }
  .features__inner {
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .features h2 {
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 48px);
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 12px 0 16px;
    max-width: 22ch;
  }
  .features__lede {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-dim);
    max-width: 64ch;
    margin: 0 0 56px;
  }
  .features__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 24px;
  }
  .feature {
    padding: 28px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-line);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, background 0.2s ease;
  }
  .feature:hover {
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.16);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.035);
  }
  .feature h3 {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .feature p {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-dim);
    margin: 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 960px) {
    .features__grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .features__grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
